tldr: The project involved implementing a database for sleep questionnaire
  responses, creating an admin dashboard for data access, and setting up a
  simple password-based authentication system. The solution uses NeonDB with
  Prisma, Next.js API routes, and Next.js middleware for authentication.
overview: The user needed to add database functionality and an admin dashboard
  to their existing sleep questionnaire application. After evaluating the
  codebase and clarifying requirements for authentication and demographic data,
  a plan was created. The implementation involved updating the data model in
  Prisma for questionnaire responses, creating API endpoints for saving,
  retrieving, and exporting data (CSV), and building a simple admin dashboard
  with a login page. The authentication system was initially designed with
  custom session management but was later refactored to leverage Next.js
  middleware for a cleaner and more efficient solution. All core
  functionalities, including database interaction, API routes, and
  authentication, were successfully implemented and verified through testing.
